<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,599,1468]" box="[264,383,599,624]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis box="[264,383,599,624]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,599,1468]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Antennae inserted above the middle of head; basal flagellomere long with a bristlelike terminal bare arista. Frons short. Eyes distinctly separated on frons and meeting below antennae in both sexes. Pterostigma on costal cell; anal lobe reduced; cell dm emitting two veins. Tarsomeres with short robust black protuberances on ventral surface; pulvilli lacking. Abdominal sclerites heavily sclerotized and punctate. Male sclerites of eighth abdominal segment fused, forming a broad ring as long as preceding segment, with small circular membranous area on ventral surface. Male terminalia hidden in eighth segment; cerci broad. Female cerci hidden in eighth segment.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,599,1468]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,659,961,987]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Male terminalia description</emphasis>
. Small, rotated approximately 90 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1050,1058,958,972]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">0</superScript>
to right, asymmetrical and retracted in eighth abdominal segment (
<figureCitation box="[791,908,1002,1028]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1692,1716]" captionTargetBox="[313,1278,335,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-105@3.[304,1282,329,1665]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Chvalaea amazonica, sp. n. 1, 2, mid leg, dorsoventral and anterodorsal views. 3, 4, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. 5, 6, male postabdomen, ventral and lateral views. 7–10, male terminalia: 7, epandrium, left lateral view; 8, hypandrium, ventral view; 9, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 10, epandrium, right lateral view. Figs. 1–2; 3–4; 5–6; 7–10 in the same scale. Abbreviations: bac scl, bacilliform sclerite; cerc, cercus; ej apod, ejaculatory apodeme; ep, epandrium; hypd, hypandrium; ph, phallus; hyp, hypoproct; ST, sternite; T, tergite." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Figs. 5, 6</figureCitation>
). Epandrium deeply cleft dorsally; epandrial lamellae united dorsally by narrow sclerotized basal connection (
<figureCitation box="[1138,1221,1042,1068]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1692,1716]" captionTargetBox="[313,1278,335,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-105@3.[304,1282,329,1665]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Chvalaea amazonica, sp. n. 1, 2, mid leg, dorsoventral and anterodorsal views. 3, 4, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. 5, 6, male postabdomen, ventral and lateral views. 7–10, male terminalia: 7, epandrium, left lateral view; 8, hypandrium, ventral view; 9, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 10, epandrium, right lateral view. Figs. 1–2; 3–4; 5–6; 7–10 in the same scale. Abbreviations: bac scl, bacilliform sclerite; cerc, cercus; ej apod, ejaculatory apodeme; ep, epandrium; hypd, hypandrium; ph, phallus; hyp, hypoproct; ST, sternite; T, tergite." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Figs. 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1233,1265,1042,1068]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–26" captionStartId="8.[264,382,1714,1738]" captionTargetBox="[310,1276,557,1686]" captionTargetId="figure-140@8.[307,1281,557,1693]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18–26. Chvalaea catarinensis, sp. n. 18, 19, mid leg, anterodorsal and dorsoventral views; 20, hind tarsus, lateral view. 21–24, male terminalia: 21, hypandrium, ventral view; 22, 23, epandrium, left and right lateral views; 24, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view. 25, 26, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. Figs 18–19; 21–24; 25–26 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">24</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1276,1308,1042,1068]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1591,1615]" captionTargetBox="[327,1262,323,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-87@10.[306,1280,303,1594]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Chvalaea masneri, sp. n. 27–30, male terminalia: 27, hypandrium, ventral view; 28, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 29, 30, epandrium, right and left lateral views. 31, 32, female terminalia, ventral and lateral view. FIGURES 33–36. Chvalaea pulchra, sp. n. 33, thorax, dorsal view. 34–36, female terminalia, lateral, ventral and dorsal views. Figs 27–30; 31–32; 34–36 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">28</figureCitation>
), occasionally this region indistinct, membranous (
<figureCitation box="[857,947,1082,1108]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–17" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[299,1248,485,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[298,1256,475,1766]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11–17. Chvalaea boliviana, sp. n. 11–15, male terminalia: 11, 12, epandrium, right and left lateral views; 13, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 14, hypandrium, ventral view; 15, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme. 16, 17, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. Figs 11–15; 16–17 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Surstyli articulated, elongate, cylindrical, ventro­dorsally directed. Hypandrium elongate, rather symmetrical, with distal margin slightly convex (
<figureCitation box="[548,630,1162,1188]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1692,1716]" captionTargetBox="[313,1278,335,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-105@3.[304,1282,329,1665]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Chvalaea amazonica, sp. n. 1, 2, mid leg, dorsoventral and anterodorsal views. 3, 4, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. 5, 6, male postabdomen, ventral and lateral views. 7–10, male terminalia: 7, epandrium, left lateral view; 8, hypandrium, ventral view; 9, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 10, epandrium, right lateral view. Figs. 1–2; 3–4; 5–6; 7–10 in the same scale. Abbreviations: bac scl, bacilliform sclerite; cerc, cercus; ej apod, ejaculatory apodeme; ep, epandrium; hypd, hypandrium; ph, phallus; hyp, hypoproct; ST, sternite; T, tergite." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[643,675,1162,1188]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–17" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[299,1248,485,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[298,1256,475,1766]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11–17. Chvalaea boliviana, sp. n. 11–15, male terminalia: 11, 12, epandrium, right and left lateral views; 13, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 14, hypandrium, ventral view; 15, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme. 16, 17, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. Figs 11–15; 16–17 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[686,718,1162,1188]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–26" captionStartId="8.[264,382,1714,1738]" captionTargetBox="[310,1276,557,1686]" captionTargetId="figure-140@8.[307,1281,557,1693]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18–26. Chvalaea catarinensis, sp. n. 18, 19, mid leg, anterodorsal and dorsoventral views; 20, hind tarsus, lateral view. 21–24, male terminalia: 21, hypandrium, ventral view; 22, 23, epandrium, left and right lateral views; 24, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view. 25, 26, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. Figs 18–19; 21–24; 25–26 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">21</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[730,763,1162,1188]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1591,1615]" captionTargetBox="[327,1262,323,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-87@10.[306,1280,303,1594]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Chvalaea masneri, sp. n. 27–30, male terminalia: 27, hypandrium, ventral view; 28, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 29, 30, epandrium, right and left lateral views. 31, 32, female terminalia, ventral and lateral view. FIGURES 33–36. Chvalaea pulchra, sp. n. 33, thorax, dorsal view. 34–36, female terminalia, lateral, ventral and dorsal views. Figs 27–30; 31–32; 34–36 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">27</figureCitation>
); dorsal bridge sclerotized. Bacilliform sclerites elongate, bearing setae; subepandrial sclerite broadly articulated with dorsal bridge. Phallus elongate, biarticulated, bent inside of hypopygium; phallic shaft gradually arched, cylindrical; distiphallus expanded basally, with simple ribbon­like, long terminal appendage (
<figureCitation box="[407,494,1322,1348]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–17" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[299,1248,485,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[298,1256,475,1766]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11–17. Chvalaea boliviana, sp. n. 11–15, male terminalia: 11, 12, epandrium, right and left lateral views; 13, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 14, hypandrium, ventral view; 15, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme. 16, 17, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. Figs 11–15; 16–17 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); basiphallus­distiphallus articulation projected outside of epandrium, visible on left side of cerci (
<figureCitation box="[613,700,1362,1388]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1692,1716]" captionTargetBox="[313,1278,335,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-105@3.[304,1282,329,1665]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Chvalaea amazonica, sp. n. 1, 2, mid leg, dorsoventral and anterodorsal views. 3, 4, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. 5, 6, male postabdomen, ventral and lateral views. 7–10, male terminalia: 7, epandrium, left lateral view; 8, hypandrium, ventral view; 9, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 10, epandrium, right lateral view. Figs. 1–2; 3–4; 5–6; 7–10 in the same scale. Abbreviations: bac scl, bacilliform sclerite; cerc, cercus; ej apod, ejaculatory apodeme; ep, epandrium; hypd, hypandrium; ph, phallus; hyp, hypoproct; ST, sternite; T, tergite." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[716,747,1362,1388]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–17" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[299,1248,485,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[298,1256,475,1766]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11–17. Chvalaea boliviana, sp. n. 11–15, male terminalia: 11, 12, epandrium, right and left lateral views; 13, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 14, hypandrium, ventral view; 15, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme. 16, 17, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. Figs 11–15; 16–17 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[764,796,1362,1388]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–26" captionStartId="8.[264,382,1714,1738]" captionTargetBox="[310,1276,557,1686]" captionTargetId="figure-140@8.[307,1281,557,1693]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18–26. Chvalaea catarinensis, sp. n. 18, 19, mid leg, anterodorsal and dorsoventral views; 20, hind tarsus, lateral view. 21–24, male terminalia: 21, hypandrium, ventral view; 22, 23, epandrium, left and right lateral views; 24, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view. 25, 26, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. Figs 18–19; 21–24; 25–26 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[811,844,1362,1388]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1591,1615]" captionTargetBox="[327,1262,323,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-87@10.[306,1280,303,1594]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Chvalaea masneri, sp. n. 27–30, male terminalia: 27, hypandrium, ventral view; 28, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 29, 30, epandrium, right and left lateral views. 31, 32, female terminalia, ventral and lateral view. FIGURES 33–36. Chvalaea pulchra, sp. n. 33, thorax, dorsal view. 34–36, female terminalia, lateral, ventral and dorsal views. Figs 27–30; 31–32; 34–36 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">29</figureCitation>
); ejaculatory apodeme fused to base of phallus (
<figureCitation box="[373,468,1402,1428]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–17" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[299,1248,485,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[298,1256,475,1766]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11–17. Chvalaea boliviana, sp. n. 11–15, male terminalia: 11, 12, epandrium, right and left lateral views; 13, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 14, hypandrium, ventral view; 15, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme. 16, 17, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. Figs 11–15; 16–17 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Cercus broad. Hypoproct broad and articulated with subepandrial sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[365,448,1442,1468]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1692,1716]" captionTargetBox="[313,1278,335,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-105@3.[304,1282,329,1665]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Chvalaea amazonica, sp. n. 1, 2, mid leg, dorsoventral and anterodorsal views. 3, 4, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. 5, 6, male postabdomen, ventral and lateral views. 7–10, male terminalia: 7, epandrium, left lateral view; 8, hypandrium, ventral view; 9, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 10, epandrium, right lateral view. Figs. 1–2; 3–4; 5–6; 7–10 in the same scale. Abbreviations: bac scl, bacilliform sclerite; cerc, cercus; ej apod, ejaculatory apodeme; ep, epandrium; hypd, hypandrium; ph, phallus; hyp, hypoproct; ST, sternite; T, tergite." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Figs. 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[461,492,1442,1468]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–17" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[299,1248,485,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[298,1256,475,1766]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11–17. Chvalaea boliviana, sp. n. 11–15, male terminalia: 11, 12, epandrium, right and left lateral views; 13, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 14, hypandrium, ventral view; 15, phallus and ejaculatory apodeme. 16, 17, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. Figs 11–15; 16–17 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[505,537,1442,1468]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–26" captionStartId="8.[264,382,1714,1738]" captionTargetBox="[310,1276,557,1686]" captionTargetId="figure-140@8.[307,1281,557,1693]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 18–26. Chvalaea catarinensis, sp. n. 18, 19, mid leg, anterodorsal and dorsoventral views; 20, hind tarsus, lateral view. 21–24, male terminalia: 21, hypandrium, ventral view; 22, 23, epandrium, left and right lateral views; 24, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view. 25, 26, female terminalia, ventral and lateral views. Figs 18–19; 21–24; 25–26 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">24</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[549,582,1442,1468]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1591,1615]" captionTargetBox="[327,1262,323,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-87@10.[306,1280,303,1594]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Chvalaea masneri, sp. n. 27–30, male terminalia: 27, hypandrium, ventral view; 28, epandrium, cerci and hypoproct, dorsal view; 29, 30, epandrium, right and left lateral views. 31, 32, female terminalia, ventral and lateral view. FIGURES 33–36. Chvalaea pulchra, sp. n. 33, thorax, dorsal view. 34–36, female terminalia, lateral, ventral and dorsal views. Figs 27–30; 31–32; 34–36 in the same scale." pageId="1" pageNumber="18">28</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1522,1868]" box="[264,366,1522,1547]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis box="[264,366,1522,1547]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1522,1868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName box="[312,424,1562,1587]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[312,424,1562,1587]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Chvalaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[616,766,1562,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ocydromiini">Ocydromiini</taxonomicName>
on the basis of a short cell cu 
<emphasis box="[1140,1155,1562,1587]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">p</emphasis>
with truncate apex, short proboscis directed downwards, terminalia asymmetrical rotated through 90º, epandrium with a pair of articulated surstyli, phallus biarticulated, ventral apodeme and postgonites lacking. The presence of a biarticulated phallus plus the lost of postgonites and a ventral apodeme are synapomorphies of the tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[875,1025,1722,1748]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ocydromiini">Ocydromiini</taxonomicName>
as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sinclair, B. J. &amp; Cumming, J. M." pageId="1" pageNumber="18" pagination="161 - 186" refId="ref5107" refString="Sinclair, B. J. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2000) Revision of the genus Apterodromia (Diptera: Empidoidea), with a redefinition of the tribe Ocydromiini. Records of the Australian Museum, 52, 161 - 186." type="journal article" year="2000">Sinclair &amp; Cumming (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. The 
<taxonomicName box="[554,704,1762,1788]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ocydromiini">Ocydromiini</taxonomicName>
is a cosmopolitan tribe, and is the only tribe of Ocydromiinae present in the Neotropical Region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1522,1868]" lastBlockId="2.[264,1323,284,550]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
On the basis of the antennae placed above middle of head, face long, eyes contiguous on the face, frons short with dichoptic eyes, Rs long and anal lobe undeveloped, 
<taxonomicName box="[1210,1322,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1210,1322,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Chvalaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Collin. However" authorityName="Collin. However" authorityYear="1926" box="[500,847,324,350]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oropezella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[500,629,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Oropezella</emphasis>
Collin. However
</taxonomicName>
, the hypandrium is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1820" box="[264,394,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Ocydromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,394,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Ocydromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
